README
******

INSTALL
*******

To install the onyxOntologyExtract script and dependencies you should be able to use the makefile.

$ sudo apt-get install libxml-sax-expat-perl
$ perl Makefile.pl
$ make
$ make test
$ sudo make install

All regression tests should pass. They indicate that all dependencies are installed and files are generated in the correct locations.

USAGE
*****

The arguments available to onyxOntologyExtract.pl are available using:

$ perl onyxOntologyExtract.pl --help

Example: extract all codes from ZIP files in a directory in home in to a single code_file.txt:

mkdir ~/code_output
perl onyxOntologyExtract.pl ~/onyx_archives ~/code_output

more info to come about formats etc.


